The '''Democratic Progressive Party''' was a [[political party]] in the [[South Africa]]n [[bantustan]] of [[Transkei]]. The party condemned [[apartheid]] rule. In the [[Transkei parliamentary election, 1981|1981 elections]], the party won one out of 75 seats.<ref>''Hela Världen i Fakta '86''. [[Stockholm]]: Bonnier Fakta Bokförlag, 1985. p. 257</ref> In the [[Transkei parliamentary election, 1986|1986 elections]] it won two seats.<ref>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/za_homelands.html#Transkei Elections in South Africa's Apartheid-Era Homelands "Bantustans"] African Elections Database</ref>

